commit.message: Factor out YamlSource.load

Merge pull request #106 from beetbox/yaml-source

Refactor YAML loading into `YamlSource` class

Always absolutify YAML file paths

Removes the decision from the YamlSource call sites.

Remove an __all__ definition

This seems to be just fine without it (these are the only names exported
here).
Move optional file check to YamlSource

Start a minimal YamlSource to encapsulate loading

Simple refactoring that just simplifies some calls to
`yaml_util.load_yaml` at this point.

commit.message:
Fix tests for Python 3.8 on Windows

Apparently, the behavior of `os.path.expanduser` changed subtly in
Python 3.8 on Windows:
https://bugs.python.org/issue36264

So our mocking of `HOME` was not sufficient.

Disable Python 3.4

It doesn't seem to be in available in the GitHub action.

Switch from Travis to GitHub Actions

I was getting weird tox/flit errors on Travis. Hopefully this is easier
to debug, at least.
Configure tox for pyproject.toml setup
Replace setup.py with flit & pyproject.toml
